    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels so pointless though. like, what's the point of trying to \"reach out\" or \"find myself\" when the person I was is just gone? there's nothing left to fix. it's like trying to rebuild a house that's already been burned to the ground. there's nothing but ashes.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It can be incredibly challenging to move forward when you feel like a part of yourself is irreparably lost. Your grief and sense of loss are valid, and it's okay to acknowledge the emotional pain. Instead of trying to rebuild a house, consider focusing on allowing yourself to heal and rebuild in your own time and way. This can involve taking small steps, practicing self-care, and being gentle with yourself as you navigate this difficult journey.",
      "source": "target",
