    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but there's nothing to heal. you can't heal something that isn't there. it's just empty. i feel like i'm just taking up space, waiting for something to happen that i know isn't coming. it's like being stuck in a loop of just existing without actually living. it's exhausting to keep pretending i'm still in here.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's as if you're stuck in a limbo, unable to move forward or backward, and that sense of restlessness and fatigue can be overwhelming. Sometimes, the most difficult thing to acknowledge is that our initial grief can become a prolonged process, and it's okay to accept that the painful emotions may be a permanent part of your journey. Letting go of the expectation of a return to your former self can be a start towards finding a new sense of purpose and meaning in your life.",
      "source": "target",
